transcript.text: Hello, welcome back to the On Print Shop Designer Studio tutorial series.
Today we will be walking you through the steps to create a PDF block path for curved text using the Coreldraw tool.
In Coreldraw, creating curved text along a block path involves using the text tool and shaping the text manually.
This method provides you with greater control over the text appearance and positioning.
Here's how you can achieve this.
Open your file in Coreldraw.
You can use the bezier tool to draw a path.
Now you can create a path with your preferred shape and then edit the path by dragging its notes and make your design accordingly.
You can set the properties of the path using the outline tool for this.
You can also use the shortcut F-12 to edit the properties of the outline.
Once done, you need to copy the path and paste it into a new document.
Next is to set the resolution to 70 to DPI and then resize the page that fits your design shape.
Set the height and width of the pages per the size of the path.
Once done, click on the OK.
Now place the path in the center of the document.
You can use shortcut P to set the path in the center of the page.
Select the path and export it in SVG format by clicking on the export button.
You will find the exported document saved on the desktop.
For further steps, open the document using Edit with Notepad.
Copy this path to paste it into the Custom Properties window in the PDF Block plugin.
Now open your PDF file with Adobe Acrobat and navigate to the PDF Lib Blocks menu.
Draw one block using the PDF Lib Block plugin.
While drawing this path, you need to consider that the block should cover the highest left of the path.
The block should cover the highest right of the path.
The block should cover the highest bottom of the path.
The top of the block is variable at the end.
Match the right, left and bottom blocks perfectly with the borders of the path.
Once set, click on the Expand All button.
Now it is time to set the block properties.
Using the property window, enter your preferred text.
In the default text area, set alignment of the text.
In addition, add custom properties using this window.
For this, click on the Add button to set custom properties.
Enter clip path in the property name.
Use zoom in and zoom out.
Set the block at the highest left of the path.
Set the block at the highest right of the path.
The block is variable at the top.
The PDF file is ready.
You can upload this file and you have successfully created the block PDF path in the Corel Draw tool.
Hope you enjoyed the video.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on onprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
